commands for linux normal file operations

Navigate!
// Change Directory Further into file system
cd /directory-name

// Change directory by going "back up" a level
cd ..

// "Look around where I am" aka list
ls .

// Remove a file
rm filename

// Recursively delete a directory
rm -r /directory-name

Permissions!
// Force permissions for a file
sudo chown $USER filename.filetype

// Force permissions for the entire directory I am in
sudo chown -R $USER .
